#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.116"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.116:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.116:0.2"
msgid "12. Lokakāmaguṇavagga"
msgstr "12. The World and the Kinds of Sensual Stimulation"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 116. Lokantagamanasutta → lokakāmaguṇa 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.116:0.3"
msgid "116. Lokantagamanasutta"
msgstr "116. Traveling to the End of the World"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: daṭṭheyyaṃ → diṭṭheyyaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.116:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti "
"vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I say it’s not possible to know or see or reach the end of the "
"world by traveling."

msgctxt "sn35.116:1.2"
msgid ""
"Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ "
"vadāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"But I also say there’s no making an end of suffering without reaching the "
"end of the world.”"

msgctxt "sn35.116:1.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā bhagavā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his "
"dwelling."

msgctxt "sn35.116:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:"
msgstr "Soon after the Buddha left, those mendicants considered:"

msgctxt "sn35.116:1.5"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṃkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:"
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his "
"dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail. …"

msgctxt "sn35.116:1.6"
msgid ""
"‘“nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyan”"
"ti vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:1.7"
msgid ""
"Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ "
"vadāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:1.8"
msgid ""
"Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṃkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena "
"atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Who can explain in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation "
"given by the Buddha?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.116:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then those mendicants thought:"

msgctxt "sn35.116:2.2"
msgid ""
"“ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ "
"sabrahmacārīnaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“This Venerable Ānanda is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his sensible "
"spiritual companions."

msgctxt "sn35.116:2.3"
msgid ""
"Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa "
"vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ."
msgstr ""
"He is capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage for "
"recitation given by the Buddha."

msgctxt "sn35.116:2.4"
msgid ""
"Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ "
"ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā”ti."
msgstr "Let’s go to him, and ask him about this matter.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.94"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.116:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu."
msgstr "Then those mendicants went to Ānanda and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn35.116:3.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnā kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one "
"side. They told him what had happened, and said:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.116:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Idaṃ kho no, āvuso ānanda, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena "
"atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti "
"vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.3"
msgid ""
"Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ "
"vadāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.4"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.5"
msgid ""
"‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.6"
msgid ""
"nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti "
"vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.7"
msgid ""
"Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ "
"vadāmīti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.8"
msgid ""
"Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena "
"atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.9"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.10"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho, āvuso, āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca "
"viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.11"
msgid ""
"Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa "
"vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.12"
msgid ""
"Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ "
"ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:4.13"
msgid "Vibhajatāyasmā ānando”ti."
msgstr "“May Venerable Ānanda please explain this.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.95"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.116:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, āvuso, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno "
"mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva, mūlaṃ atikkammeva, khandhaṃ "
"sākhāpalāse sāraṃ pariyesitabbaṃ maññeyya;"
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while "
"wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with "
"heartwood. But he’d pass over the roots and trunk, imagining that the "
"heartwood should be sought in the branches and leaves."

#. VAR: maññatha → maññetha (si, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.116:5.2"
msgid ""
"evaṃ sampadamidaṃ āyasmantānaṃ satthari sammukhībhūte taṃ bhagavantaṃ "
"atisitvā amhe etamatthaṃ paṭipucchitabbaṃ maññatha."
msgstr ""
"Such is the consequence for the venerables. Though you were face to face "
"with the Buddha, you passed him by, imagining that you should ask me about "
"this matter."

msgctxt "sn35.116:5.3"
msgid "So hāvuso, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti, passaṃ passati—"
msgstr ""
"For he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is knowledge, he "
"is the truth, he is supreme. He is the teacher, the proclaimer, the "
"elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the lord of truth, the "
"Realized One."

msgctxt "sn35.116:5.4"
msgid ""
"cakkhubhūto, ñāṇabhūto, dhammabhūto, brahmabhūto, vattā, pavattā, atthassa "
"ninnetā, amatassa dātā, dhammassāmī, tathāgato."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:5.5"
msgid ""
"So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi yaṃ bhagavantaṃyeva etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha."
msgstr "That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter."

msgctxt "sn35.116:5.6"
msgid "Yathā vo bhagavā byākareyya tathā vo dhāreyyāthā”ti."
msgstr "You should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.116:6.1"
msgid "“Addhāvuso ānanda, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti, passaṃ passati—"
msgstr ""
"“Certainly he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is "
"knowledge, he is the truth, he is supreme. He is the teacher, the "
"proclaimer, the elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the "
"lord of truth, the Realized One."

msgctxt "sn35.116:6.2"
msgid ""
"cakkhubhūto, ñāṇabhūto, dhammabhūto, brahmabhūto, vattā, pavattā, atthassa "
"ninnetā, amatassa dātā, dhammassāmī, tathāgato."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:6.3"
msgid ""
"So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi yaṃ bhagavantaṃyeva etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāma."
msgstr "That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter."

msgctxt "sn35.116:6.4"
msgid "Yathā no bhagavā byākareyya tathā naṃ dhāreyyāma."
msgstr "We should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer."

msgctxt "sn35.116:6.5"
msgid ""
"Api cāyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ "
"sabrahmacārīnaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Still, Venerable Ānanda is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his "
"sensible spiritual companions."

msgctxt "sn35.116:6.6"
msgid ""
"Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa "
"vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ."
msgstr ""
"You are capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage "
"for recitation given by the Buddha."

msgctxt "sn35.116:6.7"
msgid "Vibhajatāyasmā ānando agaruṃ karitvā”ti."
msgstr "Please explain this, if it’s no trouble.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.116:7.1"
msgid "“Tenahāvuso, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Then listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "sn35.116:7.2"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn35.116:7.3"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando etadavoca:"
msgstr "Ānanda said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.96"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.116:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kho vo, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, the Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered "
"his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail:"

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.2"
msgid ""
"‘nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti "
"vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"‘Mendicants, I say it’s not possible to know or see or reach the end of the "
"world by traveling."

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.3"
msgid ""
"Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmī’"
"ti, imassa khvāhaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa "
"vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi."
msgstr ""
"But I also say there’s no making an end of suffering without reaching the "
"end of the world.’ This is how I understand the detailed meaning of this "
"passage for recitation."

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.4"
msgid "Yena kho, āvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī—"
msgstr ""
"Whatever in the world through which you perceive the world and conceive the "
"world"

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.5"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati ariyassa vinaye loko."
msgstr "is called the world in the training of the noble one."

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.6"
msgid "Kena cāvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī?"
msgstr ""
"And through what in the world do you perceive the world and conceive the "
"world?"

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.7"
msgid "Cakkhunā kho, āvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī."
msgstr ""
"Through the eye in the world you perceive the world and conceive the world."

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.8"
msgid "Sotena kho, āvuso …"
msgstr "Through the ear …"

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.9"
msgid "ghānena kho, āvuso …"
msgstr "nose …"

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.10"
msgid "jivhāya kho, āvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī."
msgstr "tongue …"

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.11"
msgid "Kāyena kho, āvuso …"
msgstr "body …"

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.12"
msgid "manena kho, āvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī."
msgstr "mind in the world you perceive the world and conceive the world."

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.13"
msgid "Yena kho, āvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī—"
msgstr ""
"Whatever in the world through which you perceive the world and conceive the "
"world"

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.14"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati ariyassa vinaye loko."
msgstr "is called the world in the training of the noble one."

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.15"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho vo, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his "
"dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail:"

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.16"
msgid ""
"‘nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti "
"vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"‘Mendicants, I say it’s not possible to know or see or reach the end of the "
"world by traveling."

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.17"
msgid ""
"Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmī’"
"ti, imassa khvāhaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa "
"vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi."
msgstr ""
"But I also say there’s no making an end of suffering without reaching the "
"end of the world.’ That is how I understand the detailed meaning of this "
"summary."

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.18"
msgid ""
"Ākaṅkhamānā ca pana tumhe āyasmanto bhagavantaṃyeva upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ "
"paṭipuccheyyātha."
msgstr "If you wish, you may go to the Buddha and ask him about this."

msgctxt "sn35.116:8.19"
msgid "Yathā vo bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti."
msgstr "You should remember it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.116:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, reverend,” replied those mendicants. Then they rose from their seats "
"and went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had "
"happened. Then they said:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.97"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.116:10.1"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kho no, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.2"
msgid ""
"‘nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti "
"vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.3"
msgid ""
"Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ "
"vadāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.4"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.5"
msgid ""
"‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ "
"avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.6"
msgid ""
"nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti "
"vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.7"
msgid ""
"Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ "
"vadāmīti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.8"
msgid ""
"Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena "
"atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.9"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.10"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ "
"sabrahmacārīnaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.11"
msgid ""
"Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa "
"vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.12"
msgid ""
"Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ "
"ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamimha; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipucchimha."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.116:10.14"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ no, bhante, āyasmatā ānandena imehi ākārehi imehi padehi imehi "
"byañjanehi attho vibhatto”ti."
msgstr ""
"“And Ānanda explained the meaning to us in this manner, with these words and "
"phrases.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.116:11.1"
msgid "“Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, ānando; mahāpañño, bhikkhave, ānando."
msgstr "“Mendicants, Ānanda is astute, he has great wisdom."

msgctxt "sn35.116:11.2"
msgid ""
"Mañcepi tumhe, bhikkhave, etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha, ahampi taṃ evamevaṃ "
"byākareyyaṃ yathā taṃ ānandena byākataṃ."
msgstr ""
"If you came to me and asked this question, I would answer it in exactly the "
"same way as Ānanda."

